  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Physiology of migraine involving renin-angiotensin systems (RAS) has been implicated.
      Ramipril is a broadly-used angiotensin-converting enzyme inhibitor. The investigators attempt
      to test the efficacy of ramipril on the prophylaxis of migraine attacks.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
